(5, 3, 1, '', '2016-04-05 20:04:02', 46, 4224, '2f45b7f894854d8ca327c113f3aa5ec0abf909a8', '{"id":3,"asset_id":57,"title":"Ready Project","alias":"ready-project","introtext":"<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\">When transforming your organisation to\\u00a0your desired image, the design phase is to shape all of the elements to execute your new oganisational image.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0This phase brings all of the moving parts together on a single path to transform your organisation. \\u00a0With critical elements such as project management (to plan the activities and manage the technical components of your desired image), change management (engaging the stakeholders to adopt the new image), workflow mapping (mapping the inter-connectedness of the project to all areas of the organisation), and gap analysis (focus on the areas that need attention), you are assured that your transformation will take place.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><img src=\\"images\\/bigstock-Project-management-concept-in--22790042.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n","fulltext":"\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\">The components that make up <b><i>Design<\\/i><\\/b> are:<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Project Plan<\\/b> - a tool that enables you to capture, record and track all of your project activities.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Change Management Plan<\\/b> - is a tool that enables you to capture, record and track all of your change management activities; aligned to your project.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Enterprise Architect<\\/b> - is a tool that enables you to map your business'' key frameworks in the areas of information, data and business services.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Workflow Design<\\/b> - is a tool that develops simple and elegant workflows, to assist you in assessing current processes vs. future processes.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Modification Management<\\/b> - is a tool that collects details of suggested modifications to your project and provides a structure to gain approvals.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"font7\\"><span class=\\"color30\\"><b>Heat Maps<\\/b> - is a tool that allows organisation''s to identify where the impact of the changes will occur and help visualise the need for change management.<\\/span><\\/p>","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2016-04-05 20:04:02","created_by":"46","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2016-04-05 20:04:02","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2016-04-05 20:04:02","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"*","xreference":""}', 0),
(6, 4, 1, '', '2016-04-05 20:04:58', 46, 6526, 'cf60ae61e4762f3ae9dc370188df908aa473e946', '{"id":4,"asset_id":58,"title":"Ongoing Project","alias":"ongoing-project","introtext":"<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2;\\"><b><span style=\\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">Overview<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">The word <i>project<\\/i> comes the <\\/span><a title=\\"Latin\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Latin\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">Latin<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> word <i>projectum<\\/i> from the Latin verb <i>proicere<\\/i>, \\"before an action\\" which in turn comes from <i>pro-<\\/i>, which denotes precedence, something that comes before something else in time (paralleling the <\\/span><a title=\\"Greek language\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Greek_language\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">Greek<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> \\u03c0\\u03c1\\u03cc) and <i>iacere<\\/i>, \\"to do\\". The word \\"project\\" thus actually originally meant \\"before an action\\".<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"><img src=\\"images\\/design-projects.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" \\/><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n","fulltext":"\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">When the English language initially adopted the word, it referred to a plan of something, not to the act of actually carrying this plan out. Something performed in accordance with a project became known as an \\"<a title=\\"Goal\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Goal\\"><span style=\\"color: blue;\\">object<\\/span><\\/a>\\".Every project has certain phases of development.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2;\\"><b><span style=\\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">Specific uses<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3;\\"><b><span style=\\"font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">School and university<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">At school, educational institute and university, a project is a research assignment given to a student which generally requires a larger amount of effort and more independent work than is involved in a normal essay assignment. It requires students to undertake their own fact-finding and analysis, either from library\\/internet research or from gathering data empirically. The written report that comes from the project is usually in the form of a <\\/span><a title=\\"Dissertation\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Dissertation\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">dissertation<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">, which will contain sections on the project''s inception, analysis, findings and conclusions...<\\/span><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Project#cite_note-3\\"><sup><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">[3]<\\/span><\\/sup><\\/a><\\/p>","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2016-04-05 20:04:58","created_by":"46","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2016-04-05 20:04:58","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2016-04-05 20:04:58","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"*","xreference":""}', 0),
(7, 5, 1, '', '2016-04-05 20:06:43', 46, 6520, 'afdbfe8fdf1cbc350d575048b41dc50448f154bc', '{"id":5,"asset_id":59,"title":"New Offers 1","alias":"new-offers-1","introtext":"<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">In <\\/span><a title=\\"Project management\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Project_management\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">project management<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> a project consists of a temporary endeavor undertaken to create a unique <\\/span><a title=\\"Product (business)\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Product_%28business%29\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">product<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">, <\\/span><a title=\\"Service (economics)\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Service_%28economics%29\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">service<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> or result.<\\/span><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Project#cite_note-PMBOK-4\\"><sup><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">[4]<\\/span><\\/sup><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> Another definition is a management environment that is created for the purpose of delivering one or more business products according to a specified <\\/span><a title=\\"Business case\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Business_case\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">business case<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"><img src=\\"images\\/pro.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"2769\\" height=\\"1964\\" \\/><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n","fulltext":"\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\">\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">Project <\\/span><a title=\\"Goal\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Goal\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">objectives<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\"> define target status at the end of the project, reaching of which is considered necessary for the achievement of planned benefits. They can be formulated as <\\/span><a title=\\"SMART criteria\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/SMART_criteria\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: blue;\\">SMART criteria<\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';\\">:<sup><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Project#cite_note-PMH-5\\"><span style=\\"color: blue;\\">[5]<\\/span><\\/a><\\/sup> Specific, Measurable (or at least evaluable) achievement, Achievable (recently Agreed-to or Acceptable are used regularly as well), Realistic (given the current state of organizational resources) and Time terminated (bounded). The evaluation (measurement) occurs at the project closure. However a continuous guard on the project progress should be kept by monitoring and evaluating. It is also worth noting that SMART is best applied for incremental type innovation projects.<sup>[<i><a title=\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\"><span style=\\"color: blue;\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup> For radical type projects it does not apply as well. Goals for such projects tend to be broad, qualitative, stretch\\/unrealistic and success will be driven.<\\/span><\\/p>","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2016-04-05 20:06:43","created_by":"46","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2016-04-05 20:06:43","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2016-04-05 20:06:43","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","at